# Documentation Control Rules

## Documentation Location
- **Path**: `/docs` folder
- **Purpose**: All project documentation
- **Format**: Markdown (.md files)

## Documentation Structure

### Required Documentation
- `ARCHITECTURE.md`: Architecture design and decisions
- `DOMAIN_MODEL_FULL.md`: Complete domain model
- `DOMAIN_MODEL.md`: Domain model summary
- `INVARIANTS_FULL.md`: Complete invariants list
- `INVARIANTS.md`: Invariants summary
- `SCOPE.md`: Full POS scope
- `FLOREANTPOS_ANALYSIS.md`: Reference system analysis
- `ASSUMPTIONS.md`: Design assumptions
- `EXECUTION_PLAN.md`: Implementation plan
- `DATABASE_SETUP.md`: Database configuration
- `PROJECT_STATUS.md`: Current status
- `README.md`: Project overview

### Documentation Organization
```
docs/
├── architecture/
│   ├── overview.md
│   ├── layers.md
│   └── decisions.md
├── domain/
│   ├── entities.md
│   ├── value-objects.md
│   └── services.md
├── guides/
│   ├── getting-started.md
│   ├── development.md
│   └── deployment.md
└── api/
    └── (API documentation if needed)
```

## Documentation Standards

### Markdown Format
- Use standard Markdown syntax
- Use proper headings hierarchy
- Use code blocks for code examples
- Use tables for structured data
- Use lists for enumerations

### Content Standards
- Clear and concise
- Well-organized
- Up-to-date
- Accurate
- Complete

### Update Requirements
- Update documentation when code changes
- Update architecture docs when architecture changes
- Update domain model when entities change
- Update invariants when rules change
- Keep documentation current

